<paragraph id="8BE1212CFFE56838459A3073B924FA3A" blockId="16.[151,1437,1184,1463]" pageId="16" pageNumber="299">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE56838459A3073BB40FA1F" bold="true" box="[199,315,1400,1426]" pageId="16" pageNumber="299">Remarks.</emphasis>
This NT endemic species was previously recorded from six localities in the NT (
<bibRefCitation id="EFCF5CDDFFE56838418C3073BFEAFA1F" author="Cartwright, D. I." box="[1233,1425,1400,1426]" pageId="16" pageNumber="299" pagination="1 - 21" refId="ref14689" refString="Cartwright, D. I. (2010) Descriptions of 2 new genera and 13 new species of caddisflies from Australia (Trichoptera: Ecnomidae). Zootaxa, 2415 (1), 1 - 21. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 2415.1.1" type="journal article" year="2010">Cartwright 2010</bibRefCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C5E5AAFFFE5683845CA3097BB2EFA3B" authorityName="Cartwright" authorityYear="2010" box="[151,341,1436,1462]" class="Insecta" family="Ecnomidae" genus="Wellsomina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trichoptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="299" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="baru">
<emphasis id="B92AFD3EFFE5683845CA3097BB2EFA3B" box="[151,341,1436,1462]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="299">Wellsomina baru</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recorded from a further five sites in the NT.
</paragraph>
